date that the oracle returns a valid (non-zero) price. If oracle returns 0 for an asset, the contract treats it as having price of 0.", "impact": "A vault with collateral can be considered infinitely safe (if collateral price = 0) or infinitely risky (if strike price = 0), leading to undercollateralized vaults being created or healthy vaults being incorrectly liquidated.", "paths": ["1. Oracle returns 0 for any asset\n2. Vault collateralization check produces incorrect results\n3. Protocol loses funds or users lose collateral incorrectly"]}, {"id": "F-004", "severity": "High", "confidence": "high", "title": "Unchecked Slippage in Uniswap Swaps", "locations": ["Contract.sol:801-833", "Contract.sol:835-904"], "claim": "The sellOTokens and buyOToken functions use extremely low minimum acceptable amounts (1 wei) for Uniswap swaps, providing no meaningful slippage protection.", "impact": "Users can lose almost all their funds due to front-running, sandwich attacks, or market slippage when selling or buying oTokens on Uniswap.", "paths": ["1. User calls sellOTokens or buyOTokens\n2. MEV bots or market slippage causes user to receive minimal tokens\n3. User loses significant value"]}, {"id": "F-005", "severity": "High", "confidence": "medium", "title": "Unlimited Token Approval to Uniswap", "locations": ["Contract.sol:860"], "claim": "The contract approves LARGE_APPROVAL_NUMBER (10^30) tokens to the Uniswap exchange address, granting unlimited spending rights.", "impact": "If the Uniswap exchange contract is compromised or if the optionsExchange address is set to a malicious contract, all tokens held by this contract can be stolen.", "paths": ["1. optionsExchange address is compromised or set to malicious contract\n2. Attacker calls functions that trigger transfers using the unlimited approval\n3. All ERC20 tokens in the contract are drained"]}, {"id": "F-006", "severity": "Medium", "confidence": "high", "title": "Owner Can Change Critical Parameters Without Timelock", "locations": ["Contract.sol:1311-1343"], "claim": "The updateParameters function allows the owner to change liquidation incentive (up to 20%), liquidation factor (up to 100%), transaction fee (up to 10%), and minCollateralizationRatio without any timelock or governance control.", "impact": "The owner can immediately change critical risk parameters to favor themselves, such as reducing liquidation incentive to make liquidations unattractive or changing collateralization ratios to allow undercollateralized vaults.", "paths": ["1. Owner calls updateParameters with malicious values\n2. Vaults become unsafe or liquidators are discouraged\n3. Protocol funds or user funds are at risk"]}, {"id": "F-007", "severity": "Medium", "confidence": "medium", "title": "Insufficient Validation in getVaultOwners", "locations": ["Contract.sol:1291-1302"], "claim": "The getVaultOwners function returns an uninitialized array and attempts to populate it with vault owners without properly initializing array size.", "impact": "The function may return incorrect results (empty addresses or incorrect length) when called, causing issues for off-chain systems that depend on this function.", "paths": ["1. Call getVaultOwners\n2. Function returns garbage values or empty array\n3. Off-chain systems fail"]}, {"id": "F-008", "severity": "Medium", "confidence": "medium", "title": "Liquidation Can Be Prevented Via Zero Amount", "locations": ["Contract.sol:1705-1758"], "claim": "The liquidate function doesn't validate that oTokensToLiquidate is non-zero, and allowing zero would waste gas but not perform any action.", "impact": "Liquidators may accidentally send transactions with zero amount, wasting gas without any benefit.", "paths": ["1. Liquidator calls liquidate with oTokensToLiquidate = 0\n2. Transaction succeeds but performs no action\n3. Gas is wasted"]}, {"id": "F-009", "severity": "Low", "confidence": "medium", "title": "Fallback Function Accepts ETH Without Tracking", "locations": ["Contract.sol:926-928"], "claim": "The OptionsExchange fallback function accepts ETH but doesn't emit any event or track the received ETH, potentially leading to lost funds that aren't accounted for.", "impact": "Any ETH sent to the OptionsExchange contract via fallback function is trapped in the contract and cannot be recovered or accounted for.", "paths": ["1. Someone sends ETH to OptionsExchange fallback\n2. ETH is received but not tracked\n3. ETH is effectively lost"]}, {"id": "F-010", "severity": "Low", "confidence": "medium", "title": "Remove Underlying Can Be Called Anytime", "locations": ["Contract.sol:1521-1533"], "claim": "The removeUnderlying function can be called by vault owners even before any exercise has occurred, allowing them to remove underlying that hasn't been added yet.", "impact": "Although the function checks vault.underlying > 0, if underlying is somehow in the vault without exercise (due to a bug or previous state), users could withdraw it incorrectly.", "paths": ["1. Vault has unexpected underlying balance\n2. Owner calls removeUnderlying\n3. Underlying is withdrawn without proper exercise"]}]
